\section{Limitations}

The SIR model is a very simple and idealized epidemic model. We stated that the model assumes a closed population with homogeneous mixing, which is unrealistic. This assumption is a limitation to the SIR model. This then forced us to use a smaller population size in our model, which could definitely effect the outputted results. We also assume an I(0) value, along with a $\gamma$ value which was taken from a provided range of infectious dates. All of which could alter the SIR model's output. The SIR model also outputs a constant curve with no dips or fluctuations in the case values, which is unrealistic. 


